(X \cap Y) \cup Z = (X \cup Z) \cap (Y \cup Z)
(X \cap Y) = \left\{a: a \in X, ~ a \in Y\right\}
\begin{eqnarray} (X \cap Y) \cup Z &=& \left\{a: a \in X ~ \text{or} ~ a \in Y\right\} \cup \left\{a: a \in Z\right\}\\ &=& \left\{a: a \in X ~ \text{or} ~ a \in Y, ~ \text{and} ~ a \in Z \right\} \tag1 \\ &=& \left\{a: a \in X~ \text{and} ~ a \in Z, ~ \text{or}, ~ a \in Y ~ \text{and} ~ a \in Z \right\} \tag2\\ &=&\left\{a: a \in X~ \text{and} ~ a \in Z\right\} \cap \left\{a: ~ a \in Y ~ \text{and} ~ a \in Z \right\}\tag3\\ &=& (X \cup Z) \cap (Y \cup Z)\tag4 \end{eqnarray}
(X \cap Y) = \left\{a: a \in X, ~ a \in Y\right\}
(X \cap Y) \cup Z = \left\{a: a \in X ~ \text{and} ~ a \in Y\right\} \cup \left\{a: a \in Z\right\}
 = \left\{a: (a \in X ~ \text{and} ~ a \in Y), ~ \text{or} ~ a \in Z \right\} 
= \left\{a: (a \in X~ \text{or} ~ a \in Z), ~ \text{and}, ~ (a \in Y ~ \text{or} ~ a \in Z) \right\}
= \left\{a: (a \in X~ \text{or} ~ a \in Z\right\} \cap \left\{a: ~ a \in Y ~ \text{or} ~ a \in Z \right\}
= (X \cup Z) \cap (Y \cup Z)
